  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\n      \t\t\t\t\t\u003cul\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003cli id=\"Entry1\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cspan\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003ca name=\"entry\" id=\"EntryAnchor\"\u003eanchor\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cdiv\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/b2/b2ed7d912e9ef0fad75369e6efa3c991.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\" title=\"Image courtesy of Portland Museum of Art, Maine / Dovetail Design Strategists, rendering by Darcstudio.\" data-size=\"3000x1999\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cimg srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/b2/b2ed7d912e9ef0fad75369e6efa3c991.jpg?fit=crop\u0026amp;auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/b2/b2ed7d912e9ef0fad75369e6efa3c991.jpg?fit=crop\u0026amp;auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/b2/b2ed7d912e9ef0fad75369e6efa3c991.jpg?fit=crop\u0026amp;auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\" src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/b2/b2ed7d912e9ef0fad75369e6efa3c991.jpg?fit=crop\u0026amp;auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" title=\"Image courtesy of Portland Museum of Art, Maine / Dovetail Design Strategists, rendering by Darcstudio.\" alt=\"Image courtesy of Portland Museum of Art, Maine / Dovetail Design Strategists, rendering by Darcstudio.\" width=\"514\" height=\"\"/\u003e\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eImage courtesy of Portland Museum of Art, Maine / Dovetail Design Strategists, rendering by Darcstudio.\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cdiv\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003eA judge in southern \u003ca href=\"https://archinect.com/news/tag/484892/maine\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eMaine\u003c/a\u003e has ruled that the planned \u003ca href=\"https://archinect.com/news/bustler/9092/a-mass-timber-design-from-lever-wins-the-portland-museum-of-art-expansion-competition\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ePortland Museum of Art expansion\u003c/a\u003e can move forward with the scheduled demolition of an existing building on-site to make way for \u003ca href=\"https://archinect.com/leverarchitecture\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eLEVER Architecture\u003c/a\u003e’s 60,000-square-foot new wing. \u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe building at the center of the challenge mounted by the group Greater Portland Landmarks—the Children’s Museum of Maine—had seen its historic protections removed by city councilmembers to make way for the $100 million project, a move that the local group says could set a \u0026#34;dangerous precedent.\u0026#34; LEVER\u0026#39;s mass timber design beat other proposals from \u003ca href=\"https://archinect.com/adjayeassociates\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eAdjaye Associates\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://archinect.com/firms/cover/327/mvrdv\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eMVRDV\u003c/a\u003e, and \u003ca href=\"https://archinect.com/firms/cover/6135/toshiko-mori-architect\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eToshiko Mori\u003c/a\u003e and will begin work soon on a yet-to-be-made public construction timeline. (h/t \u003ca href=\"https://www.mainepublic.org/arts-and-culture/2025-03-31/judge-gives-portland-museum-of-art-the-green-light-to-demolish-the-old-childrens-museum\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eMaine Republic\u003c/a\u003e).\u003c/p\u003e\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cbr clear=\"all\"/\u003e\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cdiv\u003e\n\t\t\u003ch2\u003eSimilar articles on 